    class Network(Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.fc1 = Linear(2, 64)
        self.fc2 = Linear(64, 32)
        self.fc3 = Linear(32, 1)
        self.relu = ReLU()

    def forward(self, x: tensor) -> Tensor:
        x = self.fc1(x)
        x = self.relu(x)
        x = self.fc2(x)
        x = self.relu(x)
        x = self.fc3(x)
        return x
    

net = Network()
net.to(device)
net
    class Network(Module): def __init__(self): super().__init__() self.fc1 = Linear(2, 64) self.fc2 = Linear(64, 32) self.fc3 = Linear(32, 1) self.relu = ReLU() def forward(self, x: tensor) -> Tensor: x = self.fc1(x) x = self.relu(x) x = self.fc2(x) x = self.relu(x) x = self.fc3(x) return x net = Network() net.to(device) net

    # %%
# Bucle de entrenamiento mejorado
for epoch in range(1000 + 1):
    Y_pred = net(X_train)
    loss = criterion(Y_train,Y_pred)

    optimizer.zero_grad()
    loss.backward()
    optimizer.step()

    if epoch % 10 == 0:
        r2_train = r2_score(Y_pred, Y_train)
        with sorix.no_grad():
            Y_pred = net(X_test)
            r2_test = r2_score(Y_test, Y_pred)
        print(f"[{device}] Epoch {epoch:5d} | Loss: {loss.item():.4f} | R2_Train: {100*r2_train:5.2f} % | R2_Test: {100*r2_test:5.2f} %")
        if r2_test > 0.95:  # Mejoramos el criterio de parada
            print(f"Entrenamiento completado en {epoch} epochs!")
            break
